Description
This project demonstrates how to utilize Next.js to create and consume static APIs. It covers setting up API endpoints, fetching data from these endpoints, and testing API functionality.

Features
Call Next.js Static API

Make API
Set up static API endpoints using Next.js.

Call User List API
Fetch a list of users from the created API endpoints.
Display Data
Render the fetched user data on the frontend.

Call User Detail API
Implement an endpoint to fetch detailed information for a specific user.

Display User Data
Display detailed user information on the frontend.

Test API
Ensure API endpoints are functioning correctly and returning expected data.

Make Post Method API
Make Post API Function
Develop API endpoints that support POST requests.

Write API Response
Define responses for POST requests to handle success and error scenarios.

Get Request Params
Extract and process parameters sent with POST requests.

Apply Validation Checks
Implement validation logic to ensure data integrity and security.

Test Post with Postman
Verify POST functionality using Postman or a similar tool to validate API behavior.


Usage
Clone the repository.
Install dependencies with npm install.
Start the development server with npm run dev.
Navigate to http://localhost:3000 to see the application in action.


Technologies Used
Next.js
JavaScript/TypeScript
Postman (for API testing)
